"title": "8291: kindness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8291",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The quality of compassion and generosity, characteristic of God's dealings towards the weak and poor, and demanded of believers. The kindness is also shown in the words and deeds of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>The kindness of God</h2>\n<h3>To all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:17\">ACT 14:17</a></strong> <em>Paul to the pagans at Lystra.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:24\">JER 9:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:35\">LUK 6:35</a></p>\n<h3>To his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:7\">ISA 63:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:9\">EZR 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:8\">ISA 54:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:4\">HOS 11:4</a></p>\n<h3>To the king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:51\">2SA 22:51</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:6\">1KI 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>To individuals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:19\">GEN 19:19</a> <em>Lot</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:27\">GEN 24:27</a> <em>Abraham</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:10\">GEN 32:10</a> <em>Jacob</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:21\">GEN 39:21</a> <em>Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:8\">RUT 1:8</a> <em>Ruth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:20\">RUT 2:20</a> <em>Naomi</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:12\">JOB 10:12</a> <em>Job</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:1-2Sam9:13\">2SA 9:1–9:13</a> <em>Mephibosheth through David</em></p>\n<h2>The kindness of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:36\">MAT 9:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:14\">MAT 14:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:34\">MAT 20:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:2-Mark8:3\">MRK 8:2–8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:13\">LUK 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:35\">ACT 20:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></p>\n<h3>Its demonstration in the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:4-Titus3:5\">TIT 3:4–3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:22\">ROM 11:22</a> <em>God's grace extending to the Gentiles while the Jews are judged for their unbelief</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:7\">EPH 2:7</a></p>\n<h2>Failure to acknowledge God's kindness is a sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:7\">PSA 106:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:24-2Chr32:25\">2CH 32:24–32:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>Kindness encouraged in people</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:21\">PRO 14:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:27\">DAN 4:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:16-Prov11:17\">PRO 11:16–11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:25\">PRO 12:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:31\">PRO 14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:17\">PRO 19:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:8\">PRO 28:8</a></p>\n<h3>In the NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:13\">1CO 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:4\">1CO 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:6\">2CO 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a> <em>seen as the result of the Holy Spirit's work in the believer</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:15\">1TH 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:24\">2TI 2:24</a> <em>a necessary characteristic of a church leader</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:5\">TIT 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:7\">2PE 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of human kindness</h2>\n<h3>By unbelievers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:6\">1SA 15:6</a> <em>the Kenites to Israel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:28\">2KI 25:28</a> <em>the king of Babylon to Jehoiachin</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:3\">ACT 27:3</a> <em>the centurion Julius to Paul</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:2\">ACT 28:2</a> <em>the Maltese islanders to Paul and his companions</em></p>\n<h3>By God's people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:23\">GEN 21:23</a> <em>Abraham to Abimelech</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:29\">GEN 47:29</a> <em>Joseph to Jacob</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:21\">GEN 50:21</a> <em>Joseph to his brothers when he might have been expected to settle old scores</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:12-Josh2:14\">JOS 2:12–2:14</a> <em>the spies to Rahab</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:13\">RUT 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:10\">RUT 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:8\">1SA 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:14\">1SA 20:14</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:5\">2SA 2:5</a> <em>The men of Gilead have their kindness rewarded</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:7\">1KI 2:7</a> <em>Solomon to Barzillai</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:9\">ACT 4:9</a> <em>Peter to a beggar</em></p>\n<h2>When kindness fails</h2>\n<h3>The failure to show kindness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:16\">PSA 109:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:35\">JDG 8:35</a> <em>the Israelites to Gideon's family</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:7-2Chr10:8\">2CH 10:7–10:8</a> <em>Rehoboam to the Israelites</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:21\">JOB 24:21</a> <em>evil men to needy women</em></p>\n<h3>Failure to respond to kindness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:2-2Sam10:4\">2SA 10:2–10:4</a></p>\n<h3>Failure to remember kindness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:22\">2CH 24:22</a></p>",
